# AWS resource tagging

**What this file is:** The **only** tagging rule file for AWS in this repo — mandatory L1 provider tags, Well-Architected L2 module tags, family L3 tags, and `Name` L4 — one line per rule; no physical naming rules.

**When to use it:** Any new or changed tag map on AWS resources in Terraform, Helm values that set AWS tags, or ownership markers under **`infra/`**.

**How to use it:** Read **Format** and **Build** below; apply every line in **Rules**; read tag keys and example values from **`.cursor/rules/constants/constants.mdc`** § Mandatory resource tagging only; pair physical names with **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-naming.mdc`**.

---

## Format

| Layer | Applied via | Scope |
|-------|-------------|-------|
| **L1 — Solution** | Root `provider "aws"` `default_tags` in `infra/aws/aws_tf/providers.tf` | Every taggable resource |
| **L2 — Well-Architected** | Module `locals.standard_tags` | Every resource in a module |
| **L3 — Resource family** | Module `locals.module_tags` merge | S3, DynamoDB, IAM, logs, EKS, etc. |
| **L4 — Instance** | Resource `tags` block | `Name`, K8s subnet keys, family `purpose` |

**Merge order (later wins on key collision):** `merge(local.standard_tags, local.module_tags, var.additional_tags, { Name = "..." })`.

**Key casing:** PascalCase for L1 keys (see **`constants.mdc`**); lowercase `purpose` and `namespace:Attribute` for L3 where noted.

**Constants:** every L1 tag key and default value — **`constants.mdc`** § Mandatory resource tagging; never hard-code `ray-test`, `ray_test`, emails, or cost codes in modules.

---

## Build (mandatory)

1. Set L1 once in root **`providers.tf`** `default_tags` from **`local.solution`**, **`local.deployment_key`**, **`local.project_id`**, and root variables — keys match **`TAG_KEY_*`** in **`constants.mdc`**.
2. Child modules **inherit** L1 — **no** nested `provider "aws"` blocks.
3. Each module defines **`locals.standard_tags`** (L2) from `var.solution`, `var.service`, `var.component`, and classification variables.
4. Merge **`local.module_tags`** (L3) per resource family; pass **`var.additional_tags`** only for documented exceptions.
5. Set **`Name`** (L4) only where **`resource-naming.mdc`** requires console display or AWS integration (subnets, SGs, ALB, etc.).

---

## Rules

### Meta (all taggable resources)

1. **Constants source** — Applies to: all tags — never duplicate L1 keys or values; link **`constants.mdc`** § Mandatory resource tagging only.
2. **Solution object** — Applies to: all modules — tag values derive from `var.solution` / `local.solution`; no parallel top-level tag variables for L1 keys.
3. **Mandatory L1** — Applies to: every taggable AWS resource — all L1 keys in **`providers.tf`** `default_tags`; missing L1 is a defect.
4. **Empty optional values** — Applies to: `ExpiresAt`, `ResourceGroup1`, `ResourceGroup2`, `ResourceGroup3` — use **`TAG_EMPTY`** (`""`) when unset; do not omit L1 keys.
5. **Merge order** — Applies to: module tag maps — `standard_tags` → `module_tags` → `additional_tags` → instance keys; never replace L1 with module-only maps.
6. **No provider in modules** — Applies to: `infra/aws/aws_tf/modules/**` — inherit root `default_tags`; child `provider "aws"` forbidden.
7. **Physical names** — Applies to: `Name` tag — value from **`resource-naming.mdc`** only; do not invent display names here.

### L1 — Provider default_tags (mandatory)

8. **Application** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_APPLICATION` — Value: `local.solution_slug` — Example: `ray-test`.
9. **Project** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_PROJECT` — Value: `local.solution.name` — Example: `ray_test`.
10. **ProjectId** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_PROJECT_ID` — Value: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}` — Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3`.
11. **Description** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DESCRIPTION` — Value: `local.solution.description`.
12. **Version** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_VERSION` — Value: `local.solution.version` — Example: `0.1.0`.
13. **ReleaseDate** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_RELEASE_DATE` — Value: `local.solution.date` — Example: `2026-05-16`.
14. **ManagedBy** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_MANAGED_BY` — Value: `Terraform`.
15. **DeploymentEnvironment** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_ENVIRONMENT` — Value: `var.deployment_environment` — Example: `dev`.
16. **Environment** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_ENVIRONMENT` — Value: same as `DEP_ENVIRONMENT` — Allowed: `dev`, `qa`, `uat`, `prod`.
17. **DeploymentIndex** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_INDEX` — Value: `var.deployment_index` — Example: `0001`.
18. **DeploymentInstance** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_INSTANCE` — Value: `var.deployment_instance` — Example: `a1b2c3`.
19. **DeploymentKey** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_KEY` — Value: `local.deployment_key` — Example: `dev-0001-a1b2c3`.
20. **DeployedAt** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPLOYED_AT` — Value: UTC ISO-8601 `var.deployed_at` — Example: `2026-06-11T12:00:00Z`.
21. **DeployedBy** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPLOYED_BY` — Value: deployer email `var.deployed_by` — Example: `platform@example.com`.
22. **ExpiresAt** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_EXPIRES_AT` — Value: `var.expires_at` or **`TAG_EMPTY`** when no expiry — Example: `2026-12-11T12:00:00Z` or `""`.
23. **ResourceOwner** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_OWNER` — Value: accountable owner `var.resource_owner` — Example: `platform@example.com`.
24. **OwnerEmail** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_OWNER_EMAIL` — Value: contact email `var.owner_email`.
25. **CreatedBy** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_CREATED_BY` — Value: creator email `var.created_by`.
26. **AutomationIgnore** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_AUTOMATION_IGNORE` — Value: `"true"` or `"false"` from `var.automation_ignore` — When `"true"`, all automation must skip the resource.
27. **ResourceGroup1** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_GROUP_1` — Value: `var.resource_group_1` or **`TAG_EMPTY`** — Optional sub-grouping dimension 1.
28. **ResourceGroup2** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_GROUP_2` — Value: `var.resource_group_2` or **`TAG_EMPTY`** — Optional sub-grouping dimension 2.
29. **ResourceGroup3** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_GROUP_3` — Value: `var.resource_group_3` or **`TAG_EMPTY`** — Optional sub-grouping dimension 3.
30. **CostCode** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_COST_CODE` — Value: `var.cost_code` — Example: `CC-ARB-001`.
31. **CostCenter** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_COST_CENTER` — Value: `var.cost_center` if non-empty, else `var.cost_code`.
32. **Department** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_DEPARTMENT` — Value: `var.department` — Example: `Engineering`.
33. **AccountId** — Applies to: all — Key: `TAG_KEY_ACCOUNT_ID` — Value: `local.solution.account_id` — Example: `017868795096`.

### L2 — Well-Architected module tags (mandatory per module)

34. **Owner** — Applies to: all modules — Team or service slug — Example: `platform`, `iam`, `document-storage` — Pillar: Operational Excellence.
35. **Service** — Applies to: service-owned resources — Microservice kebab slug — Example: `iam`, `general-ai-agent`, `document-storage`.
36. **Component** — Applies to: all modules — Resource role — Example: `data-plane`, `bedrock-invoke`, `control-plane`, `attachments`.
37. **DataClassification** — Applies to: data stores and IAM — One of: `public`, `internal`, `confidential`, `restricted` — Default: `internal` — Pillar: Security.
38. **Backup** — Applies to: stateful resources — One of: `enabled`, `disabled`, `n/a` — Pillar: Reliability.
39. **Criticality** — Applies to: platform and shared infra — One of: `high`, `medium`, `low` — Example: EKS/state/IAM admin = `high` — Pillar: Reliability.

### L2 — Service defaults (mandatory when owning service matches)

40. **platform** — Applies to: TF root, EKS, VPC — `Service=platform`, `Owner=platform`, `DataClassification=internal`, `Criticality=high`.
41. **iam.svc** — Applies to: IAM tables/roles — `Service=iam`, `Owner=iam`, `DataClassification=confidential`.
42. **solutions.svc** — Applies to: solutions DDB — `Service=solutions`, `Owner=solutions`, `DataClassification=internal`.
43. **storage.svc** — Applies to: storage DDB/S3 — `Service=storage`, `Owner=storage`, `DataClassification=internal`.
44. **document-storage.svc** — Applies to: docstore — `Service=document-storage`, `Owner=document-storage`, `DataClassification=internal`.
45. **general.ai.agent.svc** — Applies to: agent Bedrock IAM — `Service=general-ai-agent`, `Owner=general-ai-agent`, `DataClassification=internal`.
46. **arch.diagram.agent.svc** — Applies to: conversion jobs — `Service=arch-diagram-agent`, `Owner=arch-diagram-agent`, `DataClassification=internal`.
47. **notification.svc** — Applies to: SNS — `Service=notification`, `Owner=notification`, `DataClassification=internal`.
48. **collaboration.svc** — Applies to: aliases DDB — `Service=collaboration`, `Owner=collaboration`, `DataClassification=internal`.
49. **frontend** — Applies to: ALB/ingress-facing — `Service=frontend`, `Owner=frontend`, `DataClassification=internal`.

### L2 — DataClassification guide

50. **internal** — Applies to: app metadata, non-PII domain data — Examples: solutions, collaboration, docstore registry.
51. **confidential** — Applies to: PII, auth artifacts — Examples: `iam-users`, `iam-logins`.
52. **restricted** — Applies to: break-glass, secrets paths — Examples: `arb-admin-role`, Secrets Manager.
53. **public** — Applies to: intentionally public assets — Default: none (public access off).

### L3 — Amazon S3

54. **S3 purpose** — Applies to: `aws_s3_bucket` — Key: `s3:Purpose` — Value: `var.purpose` — Example: `docstore-attachments`.
55. **S3 generic purpose** — Applies to: shared mount buckets — Key: `purpose` — Value: short role when `s3:Purpose` not used.

### L3 — Amazon DynamoDB

56. **DDB purpose** — Applies to: `aws_dynamodb_table` — Key: `ddb:Purpose` — Value: `var.purpose` — Example: `iam-users` (matches **`resource-naming.mdc`** purpose catalog).

### L3 — IAM

57. **IAM role name** — Applies to: `aws_iam_role` — Key: `iam:RoleName` — Value: `var.role_name` — Example: `arb-document-storage-svc`.
58. **IAM service** — Applies to: service roles — Key: `iam:Service` — Value: service slug — Example: `general-ai-agent`.
59. **IAM access tier** — Applies to: privileged roles — Key: `iam:AccessTier` — Value: `administrator` | `service` | `read-only` — Example: `administrator` on `arb-admin-role`.
60. **SolutionName** — Applies to: IAM roles — Key: `SolutionName` — Value: `var.solution.name` — Legacy companion to L1 `Project`.

### L3 — EKS, VPC, and load balancing

61. **EKS purpose** — Applies to: cluster-scoped logs/SGs — Key: `purpose` — Example: `eks-control-plane`, `eks-fargate`.
62. **Cluster tag** — Applies to: EKS-tagged resources — Key: `cluster` — Value: `NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME` — Example: `ray-test`.
63. **Solution slug on cluster resources** — Applies to: EKS modules — Key: `solution` — Value: `var.solution.name`.
64. **Subnet cluster tag** — Applies to: EKS subnets — Key: `kubernetes.io/cluster/{NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME}` — Value: `shared`.
65. **Subnet ELB role** — Applies to: public ALB subnets — Key: `kubernetes.io/role/elb` — Value: `1`.
66. **ALB tier** — Applies to: `aws_lb` — Key: `Tier` — Value: `public` | `internal` — Pair with **`resource-naming.mdc`** ALB name.

### L4 — Name tag (display)

67. **Name on network** — Applies to: VPC, subnets, SGs, NAT, route tables — Value: physical name from **`resource-naming.mdc`** Tier P rules — Example: `ray-test-platform`.
68. **Name on ALB/TG** — Applies to: load balancers — Value: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{tier}-{purpose}` — Example: `ray-test-public-frontend`.
69. **Name on data plane** — Applies to: DDB/S3 when console clarity needed — Value: full physical name from **`resource-naming.mdc`** Tier D — Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3-iam-users-017868795096`.
70. **Name omission** — Applies to: resources where physical name equals ARN/id — Omit `Name` when L1+L3 suffice and console default is acceptable.

### Automation and lifecycle

71. **AutomationIgnore true** — Applies to: break-glass, manual-only, or imported resources — Set `AutomationIgnore=true`; document reason in PR; automation must not modify or delete.
72. **AutomationIgnore false** — Applies to: default — `AutomationIgnore=false`; Terraform and scheduled jobs may manage the resource.
73. **Expiry enforcement** — Applies to: non-empty `ExpiresAt` — Ops/automation may schedule teardown after timestamp; empty `ExpiresAt` means no automated expiry.

### Anti-patterns (forbidden)

74. **Hard-coded L1** — Applies to: modules — literal project slug, emails, cost codes, or deployment key in tag maps.
75. **Duplicate provider** — Applies to: modules — nested `provider "aws"` with its own `default_tags`.
76. **Renamed L1 keys** — Applies to: all — changing `TAG_KEY_*` strings without migration plan and state refresh.
77. **Tags in naming file** — Applies to: all — define tags only here; names only in **`resource-naming.mdc`**.
78. **Missing Service/Component** — Applies to: service-owned modules — L2 `Service` and `Component` required on every module resource.
79. **Wrong Environment** — Applies to: all — values outside `dev`, `qa`, `uat`, `prod`.
80. **Secrets in tags** — Applies to: all — no passwords, tokens, or keys in tag values.

